      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-120 Identify Preferred and Secondary Suppliers
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-F1739E51-9670-4326-9FF8-B74F5A90970C" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>L3 Description- 
Identifying preferred and secondary suppliers is a strategic process in supply chain management where businesses categorize vendors based on their performance, reliability, cost-effectiveness, and strategic importance to the company. This categorization helps in optimizing procurement strategies and ensuring supply chain resilience. Preferred suppliers are those that have consistently demonstrated high performance in delivering goods and services. They often meet or exceed the company’s requirements for quality, reliability, price, and service. Secondary suppliers are alternate vendors that a company uses when preferred suppliers are unable to meet the full demand either due to capacity issues, logistical challenges, or when seeking to mitigate risk and avoid dependency on a single supplier.
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-73E97AE2-C5AA-48EA-82AF-CB9EF7C801C1" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>​​Boundary system  (CWB/Speed/ Windchill/Preferred Supplier)</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-7DBD7A72-7F88-4688-B134-C2907F04B89E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Note: Refer RAID log for system-to-task finalization information</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-B7211B47-B559-4BB0-A721-804D8528628B" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
